<p>The third day of the All-Hands Meeting began with a series of talks centered around the theme, â€˜Integrating a Diversity of Capacity Resources into dHTC 
Poolsâ€™. OSG Technical Director Miron Livny discussed Access Points, and Frank WÃ¼rthwein shared about the relationship between OSG and NRP. Additionally, 
Enol Fernandez and Gergely Sipos of EGI explained their goals of expanding their organizationâ€™s computing landscape, and Andrew Grimshaw presented on 
Lanciumâ€™s green, low-cost cloud computing. The second half of the day featured a variety of talks about OSG technology; including a token transition 
